<subSubSection box="[151,740,1410,1437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,740,1410,1437]" box="[151,740,1410,1437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,740,1410,1437]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,740,1410,1437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">
The subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Moure, 1945" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1945" box="[330,740,1410,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Hemisiella">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[330,418,1410,1436]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Centris</emphasis>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[435,565,1410,1436]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Hemisiella</emphasis>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure" box="[582,740,1411,1437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Moure, J. S. (1945) Apoidea da colecao do Conde Amadeu A. Barbiellini. II. (Hym. Apoidea). Revista de Entomologia, 16, 394 - 414." type="journal article" year="1945">Moure, 1945</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="108" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1481,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">
The subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Moure, 1945" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1945" box="[317,705,1481,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Hemisiella">
<emphasis box="[317,400,1482,1505]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Centris</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[418,539,1481,1506]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Hemisiella</emphasis>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure" box="[558,705,1481,1506]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Moure, J. S. (1945) Apoidea da colecao do Conde Amadeu A. Barbiellini. II. (Hym. Apoidea). Revista de Entomologia, 16, 394 - 414." type="journal article" year="1945">Moure, 1945</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is a lineage that comprises 18 species widely distributed in the New World, ranging from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[590,748,1517,1542]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">United States</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pemberton" box="[770,1064,1517,1542]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Pemberton, R. W. &amp; Liu, H. (2008) Naturalization of the oil collecting bee Centris nitida (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Centridini), a potential pollinator of selected native, ornamental, and invasive plants in Florida. Florida Entomologist, 91, 101 - 109. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1653 / 0015 - 4040 (2008) 091 [0101: NOTOCB] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2008">Pemberton &amp; Liu, 2008</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<collectingCountry box="[1123,1237,1517,1542]" name="Argentina" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, including some Caribbean islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Moure" box="[366,581,1553,1578]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell, 1901. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[449,498,1553,1578]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">et al</emphasis>
., 2007
</bibRefCitation>
). As it occurs with other lineages of 
<taxonomicName box="[993,1076,1554,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[993,1076,1554,1577]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Centris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the highest species diversity of this subgenus is in tropical areas of South America, where up to 13 of the known species can be found (
<bibRefCitation author="Moure" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell, 1901. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">et al</emphasis>
., 2007
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1481,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">
The species of 
<emphasis box="[374,393,1662,1685]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[419,540,1661,1686]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Hemisiella</emphasis>
) are morphologically homogeneous and can be recognized by their pattern of facial coloration in both sexes. Although some authors have considered 
<emphasis box="[963,982,1698,1721]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1005,1126,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Hemisiella</emphasis>
) as a junior synonym of 
<emphasis box="[1410,1429,1698,1721]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[160,313,1734,1757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Heterocentris</emphasis>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Cockerell" box="[330,509,1733,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Cockerell, T. D. A. (1899) Notes on the nomenclature of some Hymenoptera. The Entomologist, 32, 14." type="journal article" year="1899">Cockerell, 1899</bibRefCitation>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Griswold" box="[524,767,1733,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Griswold, T., Hanson, P. E. &amp; Alves-dos-Santos, I. (2006) Las abejas. In: Hanson, P. E. &amp; Gauld, I. D. (Eds.), Hymenoptera de la Region Neotropical. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 77, pp. 734 - 785." type="journal article" year="2006">
Griswold 
<emphasis box="[637,687,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">et al</emphasis>
., 2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Michener" box="[780,960,1733,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Michener, C. D. (2007) The Bees of the World. 2 nd Edition. Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, Maryland, 992 pp." type="book" year="2007">Michener, 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gonzalez" box="[971,1215,1733,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Gonzalez, V. H., Ascher, J. S. &amp; Engel, M. S. (2012) A new Stelis (Dolichostelis) from northern Colombia (Hymenoptera: Megachilidae): first records for South America and a synopsis of the bee fauna from the Caribbean region of Colombia. Journal of Natural History, 46, 2919 - 2934. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933.2012.738835" type="journal article" year="2012">
Gonzalez 
<emphasis box="[1084,1133,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">et al</emphasis>
., 2012
</bibRefCitation>
), the species of this subgenus form a distinct monophyletic group which is closely related to the subgenera 
<emphasis box="[1147,1166,1770,1793]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1190,1343,1770,1793]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Heterocentris</emphasis>
) and 
<emphasis box="[1410,1429,1770,1793]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[160,261,1805,1830]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Trachina</emphasis>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Klug" box="[277,406,1805,1830]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Klug, J. C. F. (1807) Kritische Revision der Bienengattungen in Fabricius neuem Piezatensysteme mit Berucksichtigung der Kirbyschen Bienefamilien und Illiger's Bemerkunde zu Kirbys Monographie. Magazin fur Insektenkunde, 6, 200 - 228." type="journal article" year="1807">Klug, 1807</bibRefCitation>
, with which it shares several morphological synapomorphies in the male (Vivallo &amp; Melo in preparation). Thus, we recognized C. (
<emphasis box="[583,704,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Hemisiella</emphasis>
) as a valid subgenus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1481,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">
The males of 
<emphasis box="[350,369,1878,1901]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[391,512,1877,1902]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Hemisiella</emphasis>
) are characterized by a spine-shaped projection on the hind trochanter, and a broad yellow transverse spot on the clypeus (covering the clypeus entirely in 
<taxonomicName authority="Burmeister, 1876" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1876" box="[953,1323,1913,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis box="[953,972,1914,1937]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[986,1116,1914,1937]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">nigriventris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Burmeister" box="[1125,1323,1913,1938]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" refString="Burmeister, H. (1876) Hymenopterologische Mittheilungen. Stettinger Entomologische Zeitung, 37, 151 - 183." type="journal article" year="1876">Burmeister, 1876</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). Females have an elliptical primary basitibial plate with the secondary plate covered with dense, short pubescence, and a dark brown to black clypeus with two very large, oblique yellow patches (which may be joined medially in 
<emphasis box="[1410,1429,1986,2009]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">C</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="109" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">
<taxonomicName authority="Perez, 1905" authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1905" box="[151,410,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversa">
<emphasis box="[151,269,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">transversa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Perez" box="[275,410,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" refString="Perez, J. (1905) Hymenopteres nouveaux du Mexique. Bulletin, Museum d'Historie Naturalle, 11, 39 - 41." type="journal article" year="1905">Pérez, 1905</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as in some specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[783,919,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merrillae">
<emphasis box="[783,802,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[815,919,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">merrillae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lepeletier, 1841" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[973,1269,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[973,992,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1005,1077,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">vittata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lepeletier" box="[1083,1269,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" refString="Lepeletier, A. L. M. (1841) Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Hymenopteres. Vol. 2. Roret, Paris, 680 pp." type="book" year="1841">Lepeletier, 1841</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). Species of 
<emphasis box="[1410,1436,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[160,281,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Hemisiella</emphasis>
) nest in pre-existing cavities in wood as in the subgenera 
<emphasis box="[971,990,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1017,1170,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Heterocentris</emphasis>
) and 
<emphasis box="[1241,1260,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1286,1426,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Xanthemisia</emphasis>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure" box="[151,288,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" refString="Moure, J. S. (1945) Apoidea da colecao do Conde Amadeu A. Barbiellini. II. (Hym. Apoidea). Revista de Entomologia, 16, 394 - 414." type="journal article" year="1945">Moure,1945</bibRefCitation>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Silveira" box="[305,537,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" refString="Silveira, F. A., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Almeida, E. A. B. (2002) Abelhas Brasileiras Sistematica e Identificacao. Fundacao Araucaria, Belo Horizonte, 254 pp." type="book" year="2002">
Silveira 
<emphasis box="[403,454,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">et al</emphasis>
., 2002
</bibRefCitation>
). However, some species, such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Batra &amp; Schuster, 1977" authorityName="Batra &amp; Schuster" authorityYear="1977" box="[932,1382,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversa">
<emphasis box="[932,951,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[966,1084,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">transversa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Batra" box="[1101,1373,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" refString="Batra, S. W. T. &amp; Schuster, J. C. (1977) Nests of Centris, Melissodes and Colletes in Guatemala (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). Biotropica, 9, 135 - 138. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 2387670" type="journal article" year="1977">Batra &amp; Schuster, 1977</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and probably others, may also nest in the ground (Vivallo, unpublished data).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith-Pardo" box="[355,579,295,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" refString="Smith-Pardo, A. H. (2003) A Preliminary Account of the Bees of Colombia (Hymenoptera: Apoidea): Present Knowledge and Future Directions. Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 76, 335 - 341." type="journal article" year="2003">Smith-Pardo (2003)</bibRefCitation>
the species of 
<emphasis box="[748,775,296,319]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[791,912,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Hemisiella</emphasis>
) present in Colombia are 
<taxonomicName box="[1209,1395,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dichrootricha">
<emphasis box="[1209,1228,296,319]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1242,1395,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">dichrootricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversa">
<emphasis box="[1410,1429,296,319]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,269,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">transversa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[327,434,333,356]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[327,346,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[362,434,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[449,674,332,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell, 1901. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[532,584,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
added 
<taxonomicName authority="Mocsary, 1899" authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1899" box="[758,1052,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="facialis">
<emphasis box="[758,777,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[793,876,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">facialis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mocsary" box="[884,1052,332,356]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" refString="Mocsary, A. (1899) Species novae generis Centris Fabr. in collectione Musaei Nationalis Hungarici. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 22, 251 - 255." type="journal article" year="1899">Mocsáry, 1899</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith, 1874" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1874" box="[1110,1361,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis box="[1110,1129,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1145,1210,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">nitida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[1219,1361,332,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" refString="Smith, F. (1874) A revision of the genera Epicharis, Centris, Eulema, and Euglossa belonging to the family Apidae, section Scopulipedes. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 4, 13, 357 - 373." type="journal article" year="1874">Smith, 1874</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, while 
